cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use cardinal-harness in your research, please cite it as below."
title: "cardinal-harness: pairwise-ratio LLM judgements fitted into cardinal scores with uncertainty"
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Sinclair
    given-names: Xyra
repository-code: "https://github.com/XyraSinclair/cardinal-harness"
license: MIT
keywords:
  - llm-as-judge
  - pairwise comparison
  - ranking
  - reranking
  - uncertainty quantification
abstract: >-
  cardinal-harness elicits pairwise ratio judgements from LLMs
  ("how many times more of attribute X does A have than B?"),
  fits globally consistent cardinal latent scores with uncertainty
  via robust IRLS over the comparison graph, actively selects the
  most informative next comparison, and stops when the top-k
  ranking is certain within a stated budget. It records full
  cost, usage, and trace evidence for every run.
